Problem Statement : 
	Write a java Program to create an integer array by taking length as
	input from the user. Take the contents of the array from user and
	store the contents in the array. Display the contents of the array by
	incrementing each value present in the array by 5 on to the console.
	Note : Use Enhanced For Loop
	
Explanation :
	We will take the user input as the length of the array. Reading the elements and Storing them in 
	the index by using the loop. And adding 5 to the content of the array and then Displaying the content
	by using the Advanced For loop/Enhanced for loop/For-each loop.